git_e17 - The enlightenment install script

This Scripts is based on Mornlenxus' easy_e17.sh
It shares some of it's ideas as well as some code.
The original script can be found at:
http://omicron.homeip.net/projects/#easy_e17.sh

Licebse: BSD licence
Get the lastes version at: https://github.com/ObiWahn/git_e17
Coded by Jan Christoph Uhde (linux@obiwahn.org)


Usage examples:

./git_e17 -s -a build 
    Get and build the whole window manager in animation mode
    and skip non fatal errors.

./git_e17 update
    Build packages that failed in the past and those which
    contain files that differ from HEAD.

./git_e17 --pull update
    Pull sources from the e17 git repository and build only packages
    that have failed in the past or which contain files that differ from
    pre-pull commit.

./git build only eina evas
    build only eina and evas show parts of the build log on errors and
    ask what to do when an error is encountered

./git_e17 --build-dir /path/to/alternate/build/dir --pull --remote raster --branch terminology update only terminology
or
./git -conf raster_term update .oO(i would create a separate config:P)


